Rating: 4
Very tasty as written, though I think my one modification in preparation takes it beyond. I find pureeing the ginger with the soup makes for an unpleasant, stringy texture. Instead, I peel the ginger and smash it using the flat of my knife (as you would garlic). I add this to the simmering ingredients and then fish it out before pureeing. This makes the texture velvety smooth. Also, subbing all or some of the milk with canned coconut milk is quite good, and I've always got half a can hanging around the fridge.

