Outstanding soup!!! What a great way to eat carrots! I increased carrots to 2lbs, increased by one half all other ingredients with these exceptions: 3 cloves garlic, 1"piece ginger, 1/4 tsp pepper flakes, 1 tbsp sesame oil, but kept the soy sauce/peanut butter at 1-1/2 tbsp each. Garnished with sour cream and minced cilantro. Don't be fooled by the deceptively simple ingredients - there is more than enough heat/kick in this soup! The previous reviewer was correct: there is no definite carrot taste, but instead a complex/bold blend of flavours enhance the carrots. Would make a perfect starter for an Asian dinner party - gorgeous colour/silky texture. Not for those who prefer a much more subtle and delicately flavoured carrot soup. Big, bold, beautiful taste makes you sit up and take notice!!! You were right San Fran: it is almost impossible to describe perfection, so that means the rest of you will just have to make this soup and find out for yourselves! Bravo Epicurious!

